misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes they must compute the difference in velocities and divide by time to get acceleration, and that reading three doubles in order will supply v0, v1, and t for the formula.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No conceptual gap detected. The code correctly implements a = (v1 - v0) / t using double arithmetic and prints the result.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: No error for valid inputs (numeric v0, v1, t with t != 0). Output matches the required sample behavior (may differ only by normal floating-point formatting).
